When implemented on a grid based upon the (u, r) coordinates, the stability of this algorithm is subject to a Courant-Friedrichs-Lewy (CFL) condition requiring that the physical domain of dependence be contained in the numerical domain of dependence. In the spherically-symmetric case, this condition requires that the ratio of the time step to radial step be limited by (V/r)Δu ≤ 2Δr, where Δr = Δ[x/(1 − x)]. This condition can be built into the code using the value V/r = e2H, corresponding to the maximum of V/r at \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
