Numerical calculation of the Bondi mass has been used to explore both the Newtonian and the strong field limits of general relativity [143]. For a quasi-Newtonian system of radiating dust, the numerical calculation joins smoothly on to a post-Newtonian expansion of the energy in powers of 1/c, beginning with the Newtonian mass and mechanical energy as the leading terms. This comparison with perturbation theory has been carried out to \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
