				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}${{\mathcal I}^ +}$\end{document}. Data are passed between the inner characteristic and central Cauchy regions using a CCM procedure similar to that already described for an outer Cauchy boundary. The main difference is that, whereas the outer Cauchy boundary data is induced from the Bondi metric on an outgoing null hypersurface, the inner Cauchy boundary is now obtained from an ingoing null hypersurface, which enters the event horizon and terminates at an MTS.
