				\begin{document}${{\mathcal I}^ +}$\end{document}, certain asymptotic quantities, in particular the Bondi news function, are only first-order accurate. However, the clean first-order convergence allows the application of Richardson extrapolation, based upon three characteristic grid sizes, to extract waveforms with third-order accuracy.

